# ✅ Interview‑Ready Explanation ⭐

> **Redux reducers are conceptually the same as JavaScript’s `reduce` method. Just like `reduce` takes an accumulator and returns a new accumulated value for each item, a Redux reducer takes the current state and an action and returns the next state.**

***

# ✅ One‑Line Answer (Very Common)

**“Redux reducers are called reducers because they reduce a sequence of actions into a single state, just like `Array.reduce`.”**

